meanings.definition: To surpass in class, quality, or rank.
meanings.sent1: She was outclassing her classmates in math.
meanings.sent2: The new restaurant is outclassing the old one in terms of service.
meanings.sent3: The little squirrel was outclassing the big dogs in the agility competition.
meanings.sent4: His determination to succeed was outclassing all obstacles in his way.
meanings.sent5: The bright colors of the painting were outclassing all the others in the gallery.

meanings.definition: To be superior to in a particular field or competition.
meanings.sent1: The champion boxer was outclassing his opponent in the ring.
meanings.sent2: Her skills were outclassing those of her teammates on the soccer field.
meanings.sent3: The clever cat was outclassing the other animals in the game of hide-and-seek.
meanings.sent4: The sun outclassing all the stars in the night sky.
meanings.sent5: The aroma of freshly baked bread outclassing all other smells in the bakery.
